    "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::importer_error_priority_loss::557c5b9e": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::importer_error_priority_loss::557c5b9e",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "medium",
      "summary": "Importer workflow cleanup/publish failures can overshadow or silently drop the primary import failure context.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "In `runImportPhases`, when workflow execution fails, later publish failures can become the returned error (`import phase transition publish failed ...`) instead of preserving the original workflow error as primary context.",
          "`errorCleanup` returns rollback errors, but transition publish failures are only logged (`failed to publish ...`) and not propagated, which can hide notification-plane failures from callers.",
