          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "waitForFailFastErrors creates one goroutine per fail-fast service that does a blocking receive from monitored.err.",
          "For healthy long-running services, monitored.err does not close until shutdown, so those goroutines remain blocked.",
          "The receive goroutines are not canceled via timeout context, only the caller select returns on timeout."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove per-call goroutines and use non-blocking/timeout-aware selects directly on service channels, or track a one-time watcher per service with lifecycle tied to startup context cancellation.",
