      "summary": "Transition publish contract is inconsistently honored (errors handled in some paths, dropped in others)",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "contract_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/shipworkflow/newship.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`EventBroker.Publish*` methods return `error`, but `HandleNewShipBoot` and `ResetNewShip` call `PublishNewShipTransition` without checking returned errors.",
          "`emitWorkflowTransitionResolved` routes publish errors through `transition.HandleTransitionPublishError`, showing a stricter contract in adjacent workflow code.",
          "This creates split behavior where some transition failures are policy-managed and others are silently lost."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Route all event publishing through a single helper that enforces one error policy (critical/non-critical) and return/log outcomes consistently; update direct `DefaultEventRuntime().Publish*` call sites to use that helper.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:06:44+00:00",
