    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_bag_overreach::1a2657dc": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::runtime_bag_overreach::1a2657dc",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Runtime structs have grown into broad callback bags that obscure real domain boundaries and reduce abstraction leverage.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go",
          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`startupInitRuntime` and `StartupRuntime` embed multiple grouped runtime structs plus many function seams, then compose long step lists with policy wrappers, indicating orchestration and dependency wiring are coupled in one abstraction.",
          "`importerRuntime` embeds storage/upload/provision groups and carries many callbacks (validation, filesystem, workflow, transition publishing), then aliases the same bag as init/workflow/publish runtime types.",
          "`workflowRuntime` embeds `RuntimeContainerOps`, `RuntimeUrbitOps`, and `RuntimeSnapshotOps` plus workflow-specific seams; this mixes unrelated concerns (container operations, DNS lookup, transition emission, upload orchestration) in one contract."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split callback bags into narrower role-specific ports (e.g., `TransitionPublisher`, `ShipConfigStore`, `ContainerControl`, `StartupSubsystemRegistry`) and pass only the required role to each use case. Replace embedded mega-runtimes with constructor-wired services per workflow path.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T14:18:51+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-05T15:27:14+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
      "suppressed": false,
      "suppressed_at": null,
      "suppression_pattern": null
    },
    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::withruntime_wrapper_chain_tax::b722131e": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::withruntime_wrapper_chain_tax::b722131e",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Repeated default/WithRuntime wrapper chains add call depth without adding policy or translation.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/state_lifecycle.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/routines/system/system.go",
          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "Broadcast loop path layers through helper constructors and wrappers (`StartBroadcastLoop` -> `StartBroadcastLoopWithRuntime` -> `runBroadcastLoop` -> `runBroadcastTickWithRuntime`), while many wrappers only perform nil checks or default resolution.",
          "State lifecycle exposes near-duplicate runtime wrappers (`LoadStartramRegionsWithRuntime` forwarding to `LoadStartramRegionsWithRuntimeState`, plus similar runtime/default split for reload).",
          "Workflow and routine packages repeat this pattern (`DispatchUploadImport` -> `DispatchUploadImportWithCoordinator`; `StartBackupRoutines` forwarding to another package) with minimal abstraction gain."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Collapse wrapper layers into one explicit public path per use case: keep either default-only entrypoints or injected-runtime entrypoints, not both across all operations. Where both are required, enforce a single boundary adapter that adds concrete behavior (policy, telemetry, retries), not just forwarding.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
