          "goseg/main.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "startup_orchestrator defines multiple embedded runtime bags (startupInitCoreRuntime/startupInitHostRuntime/startupInitStorageRuntime, then StartupRuntime, then startBackgroundServicesRuntime), each mostly function pointers.",
          "importer.go repeats the same pattern with importerStorageRuntime/importerUploadRuntime/importerProvisionRuntime and then aliases three phase types to the same underlying struct (type importerInitRuntime = importerRuntime, etc.).",
          "runtime_ops.go defines a large registry of Runtime*Ops structs and bundle builders that mostly forward package functions (runtimeContextOps/runtimeFileOps/runtimeImageOps/runtimeWireguardOps/etc.).",
          "shipworkflow workflowRuntime embeds RuntimeContainerOps/RuntimeUrbitOps/RuntimeSnapshotOps and re-resolves runtime for many operations, creating repeated seam choreography."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Collapse callback bags into a smaller set of behavior-focused interfaces per bounded context (for example StartupServices, ImportProvisioner, ContainerRuntime). Keep dependency injection at module boundaries, but remove intra-module seam layers that only forward calls. Replace phase aliases with explicit, minimal interfaces required by each phase.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
