    "review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::config_once_freezes_process_context::2d26e465": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::initialization_coupling::config_once_freezes_process_context::2d26e465",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Config bootstrap locks env/argv-derived context on first initialization call",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "initialization_coupling",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/config/bootstrap.go",
          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator.go",
          "goseg/main.go",
          "goseg/config/bootstrap_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`Initialize()` uses global `initOnce`, so `initializeConfig()` executes at most once per process.",
          "That first run reads `os.Args` and environment-derived base path (`initializeDebugMode`, `initializePaths`) and then sets global state.",
          "Startup orchestration depends on `config.Initialize()` sequencing; if another path initializes config first with different args/env assumptions, later startup cannot rebind context."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Make bootstrap context explicit: pass startup args/base path/debug mode into `InitializeWithContext(...)` and store state in an instance or immutable snapshot. Keep the process-global wrapper only as a thin adapter for `main`.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "Disappeared from scan \u2014 likely fixed",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T16:18:18+00:00",
