    "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::mutable_global_runtime_brokers::b4277f36": {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::abstraction_fitness::mutable_global_runtime_brokers::b4277f36",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Mutable process-default runtimes create leaky, hidden dependencies across subsystems.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "abstraction_fitness",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/state.go",
          "goseg/broadcast/loop.go",
          "goseg/shipworkflow/operations_runtime.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`events` exposes mutable global runtime state (`defaultEventRuntime`) and a broker (`NewGlobalDefaultBroker`) that resolves against that mutable default on every call.",
          "`broadcast` similarly stores mutable process defaults (`defaultBroadcastStateRuntime`, `defaultBroadcastLoopController`) with setter/reset APIs used by runtime constructors.",
          "Workflow/importer defaults are wired to the global broker (`events.NewGlobalDefaultBroker`), so behavior can be changed out-of-band by global runtime mutation."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace mutable process-default brokers with explicit runtime ownership per subsystem lifecycle (startup creates one broker/runtime instance and passes it down). Keep global defaults only as legacy compatibility shims behind a narrow boundary, then migrate call sites (`shipworkflow`, `importer`, `broadcast`) to constructor-injected brokers.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "auto_resolved",
      "note": "not reported in latest holistic re-import",
      "first_seen": "2026-03-05T16:57:36+00:00",
      "last_seen": "2026-03-05T16:57:36+00:00",
      "resolved_at": "2026-03-05T17:28:56+00:00",
      "reopen_count": 0,
      "lang": "go",
