      "tier": 3,
      "confidence": "high",
      "summary": "Transition publish collapses context cancellation and timeout into a single sentinel, hiding true cancellation cause.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go",
          "goseg/importer/importer.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "goseg/docker/events/events.go:147-149 returns ErrTransitionPublishTimeout for any `<-ctx.Done()` case, regardless of whether the context was canceled or deadline-exceeded.",
          "Callers like goseg/importer/importer.go:606-616 route publish errors through policy handlers, but cannot distinguish explicit cancellation from enqueue timeout because underlying cause is not preserved."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Preserve `ctx.Err()` as wrapped cause (for example `fmt.Errorf(\"transition publish canceled: %w\", ctx.Err())`) and keep bus-full as a distinct sentinel; update callers to branch on `errors.Is(..., context.Canceled/context.DeadlineExceeded)` where needed.",
