        "evidence": [
          "`startuporchestrator` defines layered runtime structs with many callback fields and tag-driven validation groups; behavior is selected indirectly through large runtime objects.",
          "`importerRuntime` embeds three grouped runtime structs with many function pointers plus multiple validator paths, forcing readers to trace callback wiring instead of domain operations.",
          "`docker/orchestration/runtime_ops.go` fragments dependencies into many `Runtime*Ops` structs and bundle constructors, increasing seam count and lookup depth.",
          "`shipworkflow.workflowRuntime` embeds multiple ops groups plus custom callbacks, creating a broad dependency surface for single workflows."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace broad callback bags with narrower role interfaces per use-case (for example, `TransitionPublisher`, `ContainerProvisioner`, `UrbitConfigStore`, `StartupServiceRunner`), then assemble explicit adapters once at composition root. Collapse validation to constructor-time checks on these narrow interfaces.",
