          "goseg/docker/orchestration/runtime_core.go",
          "goseg/startuporchestrator/startup_orchestrator_test.go"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "runtime_ops.go defines many unrelated ops contracts (container, urbit, snapshot, startup, startram, file/image/timer/wireguard/minio/netdata) and also builds concrete defaults via package-level functions like buildRuntimeSeamBundle/defaultRuntime*.",
          "runtime_core.go adds behavior wrappers (UpdateConfig/WithWgOn/Initialize/etc.) plus dependency merge/constructor logic, so behavior and composition policy are interleaved.",
          "startup_orchestrator_test.go relies on broad runtime callback surfaces for background startup validation, showing consumers must understand a wide mixed seam instead of narrower role-specific runtimes."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Split runtime concerns into separate packages/files: (1) pure ops contracts, (2) default infrastructure adapters, and (3) runtime assembly/composition. Keep orchestration behavior wrappers in a thin service layer over those smaller seams.",
